tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE hypothesis_tests (
  test_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  dataset_name VARCHAR(255),
  hypothesis_description TEXT,
  sample_size INT,
  significance_level FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE hypothesis_tests (
    test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name VARCHAR(100),
    dataset_id INT,
    hypothesis VARCHAR(255),
    result VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE datasets (
    dataset_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    dataset_name VARCHAR(100),
    dataset_description TEXT,
    data_source TEXT,
    data_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE hypothesis_testing (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  hypothesis varchar(255),
  dataset varchar(255),
  test_result varchar(100),
  decision varchar(100)
)

CREATE TABLE dataset_information (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  dataset_name varchar(255),
  data_type varchar(50),
  data_description text,
  data_source varchar(255)
)

CREATE TABLE test_logs (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  test_id INT,
  test_date date,
  executed_by varchar(100),
  test_duration INT
)

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id INT,
    user_id INT,
    result_outcome TEXT,
    result_details TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE hypothesis_tests (
    test_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name VARCHAR(255),
    dataset_id INT,
    test_type VARCHAR(50),
    test_result BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE test_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id INT,
    dataset_id INT,
    result_value FLOAT,
    result_date DATE
);
